<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1074,1573,1660]" pageId="11" pageNumber="218">
REMARKS: The female examined belongs to the 
<emphasis box="[746,835,1573,1596]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="218">savignyi</emphasis>
-group on the basis of genital morphology. It is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang &amp; Yin" authorityYear="1985" box="[603,708,1605,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[603,708,1605,1628]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="218">H. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the insemination ducts curving downwards and then ascending laterad, the rectangular bulbose sacs of the
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5822808" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5822808" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5822808/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="219" startId="12.[545,558,630,651]" targetBox="[136,1044,228,583]" targetPageId="12">
